WEBVTT

00:00.993 --> 00:03.094
<i>Previously on</i> Bones...

00:07.294 --> 00:09.462
He was a good man.
He was gonna make it.

00:09.496 --> 00:11.564
BOOTH: So everyone in
here has done time?

00:11.598 --> 00:14.033
Yeah. I told you my guys
had nothing to do with this.

00:14.068 --> 00:16.369
Oh, three more bodies.

00:16.403 --> 00:18.037
The bodies burned for
different amounts of time.

00:18.072 --> 00:19.605
SAROYAN: <i>That and the creepy</i>
<i>removal of the tattoos.</i>

00:19.640 --> 00:22.809
<i>I'm calling this</i>
<i>a serial killer.</i>

00:22.843 --> 00:24.744
There appear to be
symmetrical curve marks

00:24.778 --> 00:27.180
through the clavicles
and the upper thorax.

00:27.214 --> 00:28.247
Just like Freeman.

00:28.282 --> 00:29.348
These killings could have

00:29.383 --> 00:31.117
a ritualistic component.

00:31.151 --> 00:34.193
We found three more bodies where
Connor was being held captive.

00:34.390 --> 00:37.212
Two of them
had connections to Rockwell,

00:37.213 --> 00:38.484
one we're still waiting on.

00:38.485 --> 00:40.519
Listen to me, Alex, if you run,
they're not gonna believe you.

00:40.554 --> 00:42.588
You need to talk to them now.
Rockwell?

00:42.622 --> 00:44.256
He has a knife in the car!

00:44.291 --> 00:46.225
I don't have a clear shot.
I do.

00:46.259 --> 00:47.359
(grunts)

00:49.596 --> 00:51.564
Booth.

00:53.000 --> 00:59.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:06.839 --> 01:08.806
Rockwell?

01:11.477 --> 01:14.746
How you doing?

01:17.616 --> 01:20.651
You decided what you want
for your last meal request?

01:22.521 --> 01:25.256
I'll eat whatever the kitchen
is serving the other inmates.

01:25.290 --> 01:27.892
Aw. They'll make
whatever you want.

01:32.564 --> 01:34.599
Final 48 hours are approaching.

01:34.633 --> 01:37.869
Means you get one visit
with your family and a priest,

01:37.903 --> 01:39.904
but you got to fill out
this form first.

01:39.938 --> 01:41.205
I know the rules.

01:41.240 --> 01:43.608
I have no family and no priest.

01:43.642 --> 01:46.377
They gave up on me
a long time ago.

01:48.347 --> 01:50.581
Listen.

01:50.616 --> 01:53.151
The warden can assign you
a chaplain if you want one...

01:53.185 --> 01:54.552
I need nothing, thanks.

01:54.586 --> 01:56.687
I'm all I need.

02:15.140 --> 02:16.574
(knocking)

02:16.608 --> 02:18.276
Look, Bones, this is, like,
the fourth message

02:18.310 --> 02:20.044
that I've left you
already, all right?

02:20.078 --> 02:21.579
So just do me a favor.

02:21.613 --> 02:23.448
I'm getting just a little
worried right now, okay?

02:23.482 --> 02:26.217
So, you get this message,
I want you to call me

02:26.251 --> 02:27.718
or text me, got it?

02:27.753 --> 02:29.153
Well, this is
a big honor.

02:29.188 --> 02:31.389
Being invited to
Sunday dinner.

02:31.423 --> 02:33.191
Everything okay?

02:33.225 --> 02:35.193
Bones was supposed
to be home hours ago.

02:35.227 --> 02:36.894
She's been at the lab
all weekend long

02:36.929 --> 02:39.397
going over her findings
from the Alex Rockwell case.

02:39.431 --> 02:40.998
Why? I mean, that was
seven months ago.

02:41.033 --> 02:42.600
And she got
a conviction.

02:42.634 --> 02:44.101
Well, it's her process
before anyone is executed.

02:44.136 --> 02:46.637
You know?
She has to look at her work.

02:46.672 --> 02:48.639
So Rockwell didn't
file for an appeal?

02:48.674 --> 02:50.141
No, not at all.

02:50.175 --> 02:52.343
He even aske$ to move up
the execution date.

02:52.377 --> 02:54.779
Well, if that doesn't say
guilty, I don't know what does.

02:54.813 --> 02:56.147
CHRISTINE:
I'm starving.

02:56.181 --> 02:58.115
If I don't eat soon, I'll die.

02:58.150 --> 03:00.251
BOOTH:
Right. Coming up!

03:00.285 --> 03:03.654
Hey, what if I
sneak you a snack?

03:03.689 --> 03:06.624
Seriously? You carry
snacks in your pocket?

03:06.658 --> 03:09.861
Uh, yeah, in case of
emergencies like this one.

03:09.895 --> 03:12.296
I don't think my mom
would want me eating those.

03:12.331 --> 03:13.931
No, I'll tell you what-- she
wouldn't want you eating those.

03:13.966 --> 03:15.566
That's a good choi...
She's not picking up.

03:15.601 --> 03:16.868
Okay, Christine,
you know what?

03:16.902 --> 03:18.903
Field trip time.
Let's go get Mom.

03:18.937 --> 03:20.471
But I'm hungry!

03:20.506 --> 03:23.241
You know, if you want, I
can watch the mini-Booth.

03:23.275 --> 03:24.375
What? I mean,

03:24.409 --> 03:25.643
I'm closer to her in age.

03:25.677 --> 03:27.211
We'll have plenty
to talk about.

03:27.246 --> 03:28.980
Go, go. It's fine.
I'm good with the kids.

03:29.014 --> 03:30.548
Come on, Christine and
I will be fine, right?

03:30.582 --> 03:31.816
Okay.

03:31.850 --> 03:33.084
Listen to me then, all right?

03:33.118 --> 03:34.785
I don't want you
eating any of these.

03:34.820 --> 03:36.787
No sugar. Broccoli
only, all right?

03:36.822 --> 03:39.323
You hear me? Broccoli.

03:41.527 --> 03:44.161
Can I see those
gummy bears again?

03:51.870 --> 03:53.437
Dr. Brennan.

03:53.472 --> 03:55.172
It's late.
You shouldn't be here.

03:55.207 --> 03:57.942
He has osteophytes
on both coracoid processes.

03:57.976 --> 03:59.977
It makes no sense.

04:00.012 --> 04:01.445
Are you okay?

04:01.480 --> 04:03.548
No, I-I don't
believe I am.

04:03.582 --> 04:04.682
Is it the baby?

04:04.716 --> 04:05.716
What? The baby?

04:05.717 --> 04:07.852
No. The baby's fine.

04:07.886 --> 04:09.554
Look at these.

04:09.588 --> 04:11.088
What am I looking at?

04:11.123 --> 04:12.857
Our murderer!

04:12.891 --> 04:15.826
These are Alex Rockwell's
humeral heads and scapulas.

04:15.861 --> 04:18.529
There is increased
bone growth around

04:18.564 --> 04:20.697
the glenoid fossa
of the right scapula

04:20.732 --> 04:23.367
and osteophytes
on both coracoid processes.

04:23.402 --> 04:25.169
Okay, Alex Rockwell

04:25.203 --> 04:27.672
had untreated rotator cuff
injuries in both shoulders.

04:27.706 --> 04:29.607
And they're over
ten years old.

04:29.641 --> 04:31.909
I'm sorry, I don't get
the cause for alarm.

04:31.944 --> 04:33.778
Because he's going
to be executed.

04:33.812 --> 04:36.547
And there's no way he could've
killed Leonard Barnes.

04:36.582 --> 04:37.715
He wasn't tried
for Barnes' murder.

04:37.749 --> 04:39.050
Only the other three.
Caroline...

04:39.084 --> 04:40.351
I know.
The evidence for Barnes

04:40.385 --> 04:42.119
was older than
the others, but...

04:42.154 --> 04:43.588
Bones, wait a sec,
what are you still doing here?

04:43.622 --> 04:44.956
You were supposed
to be home hours ago.

04:44.990 --> 04:46.490
I need to find
Leonard Barnes' file.

04:46.525 --> 04:48.292
Barnes?
He was Rockwell's first victim.

04:48.327 --> 04:50.261
We found him with the others
at the ironworks factory.

04:50.295 --> 04:52.196
I know who he is.
Why are we looking for his file?

04:52.230 --> 04:55.166
Because I don't think Alex
Rockwell is our serial killer.

04:55.200 --> 04:57.168
Hold it right there, okay?
He was convicted

04:57.202 --> 04:59.437
off of your evidence
and your testimony.

04:59.471 --> 05:01.339
SAROYAN: Dr. Brennan, how long
has it been since you slept?

05:01.373 --> 05:03.341
You're pregnant.
Maybe the stress...

05:03.375 --> 05:04.875
Yes, I am pregnant, Dr. Saroyan.

05:04.910 --> 05:07.645
But that in no way compromises
my mental acumen.

05:07.679 --> 05:08.879
I am making sense, Booth.

05:08.914 --> 05:10.247
I found her like this

05:10.282 --> 05:11.642
poring over Alex
Rockwell's X-rays.

05:11.650 --> 05:13.551
BOOTH:
His X-rays?

05:13.585 --> 05:15.453
What are we doing
with Rockwell's X-rays?

05:15.487 --> 05:17.021
They were taken by the prison
doctor after he got into a fight

05:17.055 --> 05:19.223
a few months ago.
And they confirm

05:19.257 --> 05:21.225
that he couldn't have killed
Leonard Barnes.

05:21.259 --> 05:24.261
Barnes sustained blunt force
trauma to his left parietal

05:24.296 --> 05:27.131
and spinous processes
of the L1 through L5

05:27.165 --> 05:28.766
from someone swinging a pipe

05:28.800 --> 05:30.768
from a high angle
in a downward motion.

05:30.802 --> 05:32.803
Oh, my God.
BOOTH: Okay, look, everyone just...

05:32.838 --> 05:34.505
someone, please tell me
what's going on.

05:34.539 --> 05:36.507
This case was a slam dunk.

05:36.541 --> 05:39.010
BRENNAN: Alex Rockwell's
rotator cuff injuries.

05:39.044 --> 05:41.045
He would've been
incapable of meeting

05:41.079 --> 05:43.547
the force profile required
to beat Leonard Barnes to death.

05:43.582 --> 05:45.282
SAROYAN:
All the victims,

05:45.317 --> 05:47.585
including Barnes, had
that same ritualistic

05:47.619 --> 05:50.187
triangle carved into the
tissue of their upper chests.

05:50.222 --> 05:52.123
All their DNA was
found on the knife

05:52.157 --> 05:54.525
in Alex's car-- I-I ran
the tests myself.

05:54.559 --> 05:56.761
BOOTH: Okay, if Rockwell
didn't kill Barnes, then

05:56.795 --> 05:59.630
it's possible he didn't kill
any of the victims we found.

05:59.665 --> 06:03.300
Which means... they could be
executing an innocent man.

06:05.203 --> 06:08.105
In just over 48 hours.

